The Seminar of Entrepreneurship consists of three parts. A student in cooperation with a science laboratory elaborates and developes a science-intensive product. In seminars the participants of the course discuss their problems and activities and analyze their results.
In the first part of the course the student in collaboration with the laboratory finds a problem which can be solved with material development, and chooses respective product. He/she studies the solutions for similar problems and close products, and then makes plans for technology of fabrication, necessary equipment and source materials of the chosen product. He/she establishes a small business, or plays through establishment of the business.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is providing students with the knowledge, skills and experience for commercialization of applications of materials science, planning, establishment and running of a science-intensive small business.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the first part of the Seminar of Entreprenuership, the student has found a laboratory which wants to cooperate in elaboration and development of a science-intensive product. The student has made a plan for fabrication of this product, and established a small business, or played through establishment of a small business.
